        /// <br/>
        /// <br/>**Connection URL:** `ws://&lt;host&gt;/ws/analytics`
        /// <br/>
        /// <br/>**Auth:** `Sec-WebSocket-Protocol: auth.&lt;idToken&gt;` (same mechanism as all WebSocket endpoints – see the *Chats – WebSocket* tag description for details)
        /// <br/>
        /// <br/>**Role requirement:** `admin` or `superadmin` only. Connections from `learner` accounts are closed with code `1008`.
        /// <br/>
        /// <br/>**Session flow:**
        /// <br/>1. Connect (server accepts if token is valid and role is admin/superadmin).
        /// <br/>2. Send one `AnalyticsSessionInitPayload` JSON message.
        /// <br/>3. Receive a stream of `response.content_delta` events (answer text).
        /// <br/>4. Receive a single `response.analytics` event with the full structured
        /// <br/>   analytics response.
        /// <br/>
        /// <br/>5. Receive `response.completed` – the server closes the connection.
        /// <br/>
        /// <br/>The session has a **120-second idle timeout**.  Only one inbound message per session is accepted; subsequent messages are ignored.
        /// <br/>
        /// <br/>An interactive tester is available at [/ws-tester.html](/ws-tester.html).
        /// </remarks>
        /// <param name="sec_WebSocket_Protocol">WebSocket sub-protocol carrying the Cognito ID token. Value must be `auth.&lt;idToken&gt;`.  The authenticated user must have role `admin` or `superadmin`.</param>
        /// <exception cref="ApiException">A server side error occurred.</exception>
